steps.content:
Simplify the equation from Step 1:
\begin{align}
x^2 - 1 &= 9 - x^2 \\
\end{align}
Now, add $x^2$ to both sides of the equation:
\begin{align}
2x^2 - 1 &= 9 \\
\end{align}
Finally, add 1 to both sides:
\begin{align}
2x^2 &= 10 \\
\end{align}
Divide both sides by 2:
\begin{align}
x^2 &= 5 \\
\end{align}
Take the square root of both sides:
\begin{align}
x &= \sqrt{5} \\
\end{align}

